All right, well, so we have the magic solution for every single one of you that put your hands down.

00:59.120 --> 01:08.920
How many of you have heard of fiscal sponsorship? Oh, all right, well, you know the end of the talk,

01:08.920 --> 01:14.280
but Madeline, what is fiscal sponsorship? This magical thing that might help everyone in this room.

01:14.280 --> 01:19.800
Fiscal sponsorship is indeed a magical thing and it leverages economies of scale so that we build

01:19.920 --> 01:25.320
shared operational and administrative infrastructure so that projects can thrive. What that means is

01:25.320 --> 01:30.120
that you get to work under the umbrella of an organization who will handle things like your payroll,

01:30.120 --> 01:34.760
like your taxes, like your insurance, things that take up so much time and energy and take away

01:34.760 --> 01:39.320
from the ability that you have to invest in the things that you care about most. And it's not just

01:39.320 --> 01:43.480
that when you participate in an organization, you get extended some of the benefits of being in

01:43.480 --> 01:48.920
part of a nonprofit. In the US, for example, that's a 501c3, where you'll yield certain tax benefits.

01:49.480 --> 01:55.400
But what else do you get out of a fiscal sponsorship, Angela? Is it just operational and administrative infrastructure?

01:55.400 --> 02:01.640
Boring, shmoring, taxes, blah, payroll. The most interesting thing to me, I'm a people person,

02:01.640 --> 02:07.400
can you tell? I like people. Yes, I like people. Shocking. I think it's the people, right? Like,

02:07.400 --> 02:13.400
as we build all of these open source tech products, like everyone's head down, oh my god, I gotta get

02:13.400 --> 02:20.120
this code out. It's gonna break. What if you could actually come together with other people

02:20.120 --> 02:25.000
as we're doing here, but do it on a regular basis? You talk about the challenges you're facing. You

02:25.000 --> 02:29.880
share best practice, lessons learned. You talk about which funders might give you some money.

02:31.160 --> 02:36.680
The ability to actually come together and build camaraderie and build products that have shared

02:36.680 --> 02:41.800
ethos and mission alignment is, in my opinion, one of the best parts of being under a mission

02:41.800 --> 02:47.640
aligned fiscal sponsor. So we are very excited to answer any questions if you have them. We

02:47.640 --> 02:53.240
represent a fiscal sponsor. We are based in the US, but there are European fiscal sponsors as well.

02:53.240 --> 02:57.960
So for those who might not be familiar with them, they're actually some regional. Regionally, I

